Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, mild hyperkalemia, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria with glycosuria and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function, possible acute or chronic kidney disease, and metabolic derangement (possibly diabetic ketoacidosis). Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity) further support renal involvement. Mildly elevated ALT may indicate hepatic stress. Immediate clinical evaluation is recommended.
